# ============================================================
# gateway/.env.example — minimal env template for the gateway
# container (vps-ifix-vm /opt/ai-gateway-dev/.env).
# ============================================================
#
# Companion to:
#   - gateway/.env.prod.example     — full prod (n8n-ia-vm) contract
#   - gateway/.env.portainer.example — Portainer stack UI contract
#   - pod/.env.example              — pod-side parity (weights + STT envs)
#
# This file documents ONLY the env vars introduced or restored by
# Phase 11.2 (STT cascade Gemini + Groq Whisper, plus pod-image
# weights restored after Phase 11.1 revert).
#
# Operators populate AUTH_BEARER + SHA256 values from:
#   ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md            — Gemini, Groq (rotation log)
#   `mc cp ifix/ai-gateway/...`    — Whisper weights tarball SHA-256
#
# NEVER commit populated values. Every entry below is empty,
# a <placeholder>, or a literal default safe to commit.
# ============================================================

# ============================================================
# --- Phase 11.2: pod-image pin (D-B1 LOCKED) + Whisper weights
# ============================================================
# Speaches image — pinned verbatim per Phase 06.7-06.8 UAT evidence
# (HF_HUB_CACHE workaround known). Do NOT bump without revisiting
# CLAUDE.md note `primary-gpu-shape-06.8-final` and pod UAT 06.8.
PRIMARY_SPEACHES_IMAGE=ghcr.io/speaches-ai/speaches:0.9.0-rc.3-cuda-12.6.3

# MinIO object key for the Whisper-large-v3 weights tarball. Restored
# in Phase 11.2 after Phase 11.1 removed local-stt (D-B2 = faster-whisper
# Systran/faster-whisper-large-v3). The pod's onstart.sh downloads from
# MinIO and verifies SHA-256 before booting Speaches.
PRIMARY_WHISPER_WEIGHTS_KEY=whisper-large-v3/v1.0.0/model.tar.gz
# FAIL-FAST passthrough — no envOr default. buildPrimaryCreateRequest
# rejects empty value at build time (Plan 02 review consensus action #6).
PRIMARY_WHISPER_WEIGHTS_SHA256=<64-hex-digits-from-upload>

# ============================================================
# --- Phase 11.2: STT tier-1 cascade (D-B7 + D-B8)
# ============================================================
# Slot-named so operator can swap a provider into the slot without
# renaming envs. Current assignment:
#   slot 1 = Gemini 2.5 Flash Lite (cheapest, ~$0.05/h batch)
#   slot 2 = Groq Whisper-large-v3 (REUSES OpenAI-compat director)
#
# See docs/RUNBOOK-OPS.md for minting + rotation procedures and the
# D-B10 verbatim gate command:
#   ssh vps-ifix-vm 'docker inspect ai-gateway-dev \
#     --format "{{range .Config.Env}}{{println .}}{{end}}" \
#     | grep UPSTREAM_STT_FALLBACK_{1,2}_AUTH_BEARER'
#
# AUTH_BEARER values are sensitive — gateway Config tags them
# json:"-" (T-11.2-CFG mitigation); never log them.
# ============================================================

# slot 1 — Gemini (D-B3, D-B7)
# Director: gateway/internal/proxy/gemini_stt_director.go
#   - Translates OpenAI multipart → Gemini JSON (inline_data base64).
#   - Header: x-goog-api-key (NOT Authorization: Bearer — Pitfall 3).
# Breaker: cooldown_s=120 via upstreams.circuit_config JSONB (D-B11).
UPSTREAM_STT_FALLBACK_1_URL=https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta
# operator: mint key at https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
UPSTREAM_STT_FALLBACK_1_AUTH_BEARER=
UPSTREAM_STT_FALLBACK_1_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash-lite

# slot 2 — Groq Whisper (D-B8)
# Director: REUSES BuildOpenAIWhisperDirector (Groq endpoint is
# byte-identically OpenAI-compatible — zero new adapter code).
# Breaker: default cooldown (no custom circuit_config row).
UPSTREAM_STT_FALLBACK_2_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai
# operator: mint key at https://console.groq.com/keys
UPSTREAM_STT_FALLBACK_2_AUTH_BEARER=
UPSTREAM_STT_FALLBACK_2_MODEL=whisper-large-v3
